<emphasis id="B975045FFFBFF82CFF60F7D74FFBF795" box="[136,233,2056,2077]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="148">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C01A3CEFFBFF82CFF12F7D74EB6F795" box="[250,420,2056,2077]" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="148" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="glacierum">
<emphasis id="B975045FFFBFF82CFF12F7D74EB6F795" box="[250,420,2056,2077]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="148">Bryum glacierum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by (1) dark red-brown, obconic or ovate bulbils with peg-like leaf primordia, densely clustered in the leaf axils of sterile shoots, (2) broadly ovate unbordered leaves, with rhombic to rhomboidal distal medial cells, and (3) gemmiform to rounded-julaceous stems with imbricate leaves.
</paragraph>
